This paper deals with probabilistic model checking, which involves analyzing the behavior of probabilistic systems. The paper specifically focuses on Markov chains and Markov decision processes, which are commonly studied in the area of logic and computation (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of automata, which are commonly used in the study of formal languages and automata theory (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of a prototype tool, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper involves the use of algorithms and data structures to efficiently analyze probabilistic systems, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
